  "title": "Marketing Executive",
  "description": "<ul>\n  <li>Assist in planning and executing marketing initiatives across digital, print, and retail platforms.</li>\n  <li>Coordinate in-store promotions, product launches, and brand events.</li>\n  <li>Work closely with the sales and product teams to ensure marketing strategies align with business objectives.</li>\n  <li>Develop compelling content for social media, email newsletters, websites, and product brochures.</li>\n  <li>Conduct research on market trends and competitive landscape to identify new opportunities.</li>\n  <li>Track and analyze marketing campaign performance, generating reports on ROI, engagement, and sales effectiveness.</li>\n  <li>Oversee the inventory and distribution of marketing materials and product samples.</li>\n  <li>Communicate with external agencies, designers, and media partners as required.</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong>Requirements:</strong></p>\n<ul>\n  <li>Diploma or Degree in Marketing, Business, Communications, or a related field.</li>\n  <li>1–2 years of marketing experience is preferred.</li>\n  <li>Keen interest in consumer goods, especially home appliances.</li>\n  <li>Familiar with basic digital marketing tools (e.g., Meta Ads, Google Analytics, Mailchimp, Canva).</li>\n  <li>Strong writing and communication skills.</li>\n  <li>Organized, detail-oriented, and able to multitask effectively.</li>\n  <li>A collaborative team player with a growth mindset.</li>\n</ul>\n<p>We regret only shortlisted candidates will be contacted. All applications will be handled confidentially. By submitting your application, you agree to the collection, use, retention, and disclosure of your personal information to prospective employers.</p>\n<p>Wecruit Pte Ltd</p>\n<p>EA License No. 20C0270</p>",
